        "message": "LU-19813 build: detect arch with $(uname -m) in O2IBDIR_PATH\n\nOn a ppc64le system, ${target_cpu} outputs powerpc64le\ninstead of ppc64le, which causes an incorrect O2IBDIR_PATH.\nThis patch fixes the above issue by using $(uname -m)\ninstead of ${target_cpu} to detect the system architecture.\n\nChange-Id: I5aacd0b1b3dbfa0dc469e58d71972fc64c4b3bd0\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nFixes: aea9738642 (\"LU-18002 build: proper MOFED detection with multiple installations\")\nSigned-off-by: Jian Yu <yujian@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-on: https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/65051\nReviewed-by: Xiao Yang <xyang@ddn.com>\nTested-by: jenkins <devops@whamcloud.com>\nTested-by: Maloo <maloo@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <green@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Andreas Dilger <adilger@thelustrecollective.com>\n"
